Title: Stop Letting External Events Control Your System (Do This Instead)
Description:
Hi, I'm James. And ordinarily, I don't like dealing in absolutes. With a title like "you should ALWAYS", you might struggle to believe that. But it's honestly that important.

In this video you'll learn the importance of an anti-corruption layer, or at the very least not letting a data structure controlled by an external system drive business logic in your internal system.

01:03 - The Problem
01:54 - What Is An Anti-Corruption Layer?

Title: Understanding Cursor Pagination and Why It's So Fast (Deep Dive)
Description: While offset pagination is widely used, cursor-based pagination offers significant performance advantages - my tests show a 17x speedup when paginating through a million-record dataset in PostgreSQL. Let's take a deep dive into cursor pagination, compare it with offset pagination, and examine the SQL execution plans.
